CBFI Tutorial

Sejong Oh

2021 7 26

1. Introduction

CBFI (Prediction Case based-Feature importance and interaction) package is for observing feature importance and interaction for given prediction model. It supports both classification and regression model. This tutorial shows usages of functions that CBFI supports.

2. Install CBFI package

To install CBFI package, you may be required Rtoools SW. In that case, you can get get Rtoools at https://cran.r-project.org/bin/windows/Rtools/.

After install CBFI package, please restart R session.

install.packages(
  "https://bitldku.github.io/home/sw/CBFI/CBFI_1.0.0.tar.gz", 
  repos = NULL, type = "source")
## 'C:/Users/DKU/Documents/R/win-library/4.1'  () .
## ( 'lib'   )
#.rs.restartR()  # restart R session 

library(CBFI)   # load CBFI package

3. Datasets and prediction models for test

In this tutorial, We use two datsets Bostion and iris for regression and classification, respectively. lm and svm functions are used for building prediction models.

4. Feature importance plot

[For classification model]

Feature importance plot on iris dataset. More iteration(itr), more accurate result.

[For regression model]

Feature importance plot on Boston dataset.

result <- CB_FeatureImp(model.lm, train=Boston, target.name="medv", itr=50, task="regression")
CB_plot.imp(result, combine=F)

CB_plot.imp(result, combine=T)

5. Feature interaction plot

[For classification model]

Feature interaction plot for between two features in iris dataset.

result <- CB_FeatureInteract(model.svm, train=iris, target.name="Species", F1="Petal.Width", F2=NULL, itr=50, task="classification")
## End class:  setosa ... 
## End class:  versicolor ... 
## End class:  virginica ...
CB_plot.interact(result, class="_all_")

CB_plot.interact(result, class="setosa")

result2 <- CB_FeatureInteract(model.svm, train=iris, target.name="Species", F1="Petal.Width", F2="Petal.Length", itr=50, task="classification")
## End class:  setosa ... 
## End class:  versicolor ... 
## End class:  virginica ...
CB_plot.interact(result2, class="_all_")

CB_plot.interact(result2, class="versicolor")

6. Feature interaction network

[For classification model]

FIobj <- CB_FItable(model.svm, iris, "Species", itr=50, task="classification")
# print(FIobj)
CB_plot.FIgraph( gtype="S", FIobj=FIobj, task="classification", class="_all_",
             show.edge.weight=TRUE, seed=104)
## th:  0.1456667

CB_plot.FIgraph( gtype="S", FIobj=FIobj, task="classification", class="setosa",
             show.edge.weight=TRUE, seed=104)
## th:  0.066

[For regression model]

FIobj <- CB_FItable(model.lm, Boston, "medv", itr=50, task="regression")
# print(FIobj)
CB_plot.FIgraph(gtype="S", FIobj, task="regression", class="_all_",
                    show.edge.weight=TRUE, seed=104, th=NULL)
## th:  0.4065256

8. Feature contribution plot

[For classification model]

result = CB_FeatureInteract(model.svm, iris, "Species",  F1="Petal.Width", F2="Petal.Length", itr=10, task="classification")
CB_plot.contribute(result, class="_all_")

CB_plot.contribute(result, class="setosa")
